set.html: Hey. Hey. Hey. Look what we've here!
You look pretty rich. Can you help two poor guys?
Not only we ARE poor little guys...
You aren't very chatty, are you?
My name is Blamage but I'm sure you already know that.
I passed most of my life in the South village...
...where humans lives peacefully. Well. Not all humans.
Commercial routes are blocked by Rogues...
A group of humans thieves that placed their base...
We've just to go south without being caught!
Sorry pals. We're repairing the bridge.
We'll come back here later, Blamage.
Yes. And I surely know that there isn't any bridge.
How is possible that a Blamage is here?!
Looks like I managed to leave this place...
That's quite a failure, isn't it?
Eh eh eh. There isn't anything to cheer up.
He'll kill you guys for sure...
Let them go. They are going on the west, at their base.
All these tresaure chests scattered around...
Why they are here in first place?
I've studied that in war ammunitions and...
It can be used by soldiers in critical conditions.
But... we aren't in war, as far as I know...
I can't believe that you guys came here.
We're going to kill you and...
Why you have to kill us?
Why everybody is trying to kill us?
Damn bastard. Your stupid trick will not work here.
Little bastards! You and your Gods!
Well, little hero, we SURELY have faith.
...and that's why we're doing all this.
I'm going to kill a Blamage.
You've never got your hands dirty...
Not by blood from the village, little black mage.
I'll never know why you're so obsessed...
I'm getting less and less curious.
So. Let's do it. You've escaped...
I prefer to decide by myself...
But I had to try to stop you.
Tell to your Gods to stop...
Loving us this much. Ah ah ah...
I hope someone will stop you...
Let's go to the village now.
DON'T TELL US WHAT WE HAVE TO DO!!
We're going to take your boss down...
Whatever I'll do, Gods' word will be the truth.
You have to tell me what's happening.
Gods sent you to save this world...
And I'll guide you in your mission.
There isn't really anything more to know.
These rogues are keeping us in our village.
Many of us died without seeing nothing more...
...than the village walls, fearing to go out.
Whatever your mission is, I must free my village.
Me, my mother and my sisters were never able...
...to leave the village to find my father.
He managed to escape years ago and never came back.
I must find him and his answers.
We're just in front of my village.
Ptew! That was a long way!
Ah ah ah! That's right. We've to find my sister Whimage.
She should be there, probably on the south side.
Wait. Can I ask you something?
Why the the king of rogues called you 'a Blamage'?
Ah ah ah! My fault! I forgot to tell you that...
...all males of the village are called Blamage...
We don't have our own names but...
...don't worry! We'll find my sister pretty easily!
